<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-29T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="308" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9776: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-29T15:00:00-04:00">August 29, 1937—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>192. Your 549, August 28, 7 p.m., has been repeated to Tokyo for
                            communication to the interested Ambassadors. Ambassador Grew has been
                            informed that the Department approves of his associating himself with
                            his interested colleagues in an appropriate approach to the Japanese
                            Government on this matter.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>